Class BetterRectangle

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.shape.Shape
        • javafx.scene.shape.Rectangle
          • paint.BetterRectangle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SelectionRectangle

    public class BetterRectangle
extends javafx.scene.shape.Rectangle
    A more efficient rectangle shape that can handle negative dimensions. JavaFX' default Rectangle does not support negative width and height! This one does! It works exactly the same as a regular Rectangle object. To set the rectangle's width or height, use setRelativeWidth() or setRelativeHeight() instead of the usual setWidth() and setHeight(). TranslateX and TranslateY will be automatically modified so as the rectangle looks like having negative dimensions. X and Y position will not move, but it is possible to have the top-left point coordinates by calling getAbsX() and getAbsY().

    • Method Detail

      • setRelativeWidth

        public void setRelativeWidth(double w)
        Change rectangle's width. Accepts negative values. If the given width is negative, the rectangle will be translated on the X axis and the absolute width will be applied.
        Parameters:
        w - the new width.

      • setRelativeHeight

        public void setRelativeHeight(double h)
        Change rectangle's height. Accepts negative values. If the given height is negative, the rectangle will be translated on the Y axis and the absolute height will be applied.
        Parameters:
        h - the new height.
